      "role": "user",
      "content": "i dont know... neurological phenomena feels like a cop out. it was too consistent. the light hit the window at the exact same angle twice, like it was looping. i've been reading about simulation theory online and some people say these kinds of \"glitches\" are actually evidence that we're living in a programmed environment. i know it sounds crazy but what if the \"stutter\" i saw was actually a processing error in the system? does that actually make sense or am i just tripping?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
